The DA is not convinced parliament will run a thorough process for considering thousands of submissions shared in consultation over the National Health Insurance. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The DA said the coronavirus pandemic has confirmed the country's health system is not ready for the National Health Insurance. The criticism comes despite President Cyril Ramaphosa having praised some hospitals for putting building blocks in place to get ready for the country's vision of universal healthcare. WATCH: Health Minister explains NHI Bill Public hearings have been held in all provinces and members of the public have made written submissions against a deadline set for earlier this year. The DA is not convinced Parliament will run a thorough process for considering thousands of these submissions.